  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Associate",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a Dispute Resolution Associate (2–4 PQE) to join an <strong>entrepreneurial disputes platform</strong> in Singapore of an international law firm. This role is ideal for an associate who is not afraid of ambition and who wants to play a meaningful role in <strong>building a disputes practice</strong> rather than simply servicing one.</p><p>The successful candidate will work on high-value and complex disputes, including commercial and cross-border matters, and will be given meaningful responsibility with appropriate supervision and direct partner mentorship.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p>• Act on a broad range of contentious matters, including commercial litigation and arbitration</p><p>• Assist with and manage legal proceedings, including pleadings, interlocutory applications, discovery,affidavits, and trials</p><p>• Conduct legal research and prepare written submissions, affidavits, and legal opinions</p><p>• Support senior lawyers in hearings and oral advocacy, with opportunities to develop advocacy skills</p><p>• Liaise with clients, experts, opposing counsel, and courts or arbitral tribunals</p><p>• Contribute to case strategy, dispute risk assessments, and settlement discussions</p><h3>Qualifications and Requirements</h3><p>• Singapore-qualified lawyer with 2–4 years of post-qualification experience</p><p>• Experience in court litigation and/or arbitration gained in a reputable law firm</p><p>• Demonstrated interest in advocacy and dispute resolution work</p><p>• Strong drafting, research, and analytical skills</p><p>• Ability to manage matters efficiently and work well under pressure</p><p>• Chinese language skills (written or conversational) are an advantage but not essential for communicating withChinese clients and understanding Chinese language documents</p><p>• Strong interpersonal skills and a collaborative, professional approach</p><h3>Why Join Us</h3><p>• Exposure to substantive and high-quality disputes work rather than narrow task-based roles</p><p>• Opportunities to develop advocacy and hearing experience as part of a litigation-focused practice</p><p>• Close partner and senior associate mentorship in a flat and hands-on team structure</p><p>• Involvement in strategic, cross-border, and complex matters</p><p>• A professional, collegiate environment with clear opportunities for growth and responsibility</p>",
